$Date$
                             kvoctrain

        helps you train your own vocabulary in different languages
        
==================================================================

This package is compilable for KDE1 *AND* KDE2.

To determine the target version for compilation for see
README.kde1x-kde2x.

==================================================================

This tool is intended as a replacement for the old recommendation, to
excercise your vocabulary with little sheets of paper and a box.

You remember: write the original expression on the front side of a sheet
and the translation on the back. Then look at the first sheet. If you know
the translation, put it away. If you failed, put it back into the box.

To find out more about this little application choose HELP in its main menu.

To install, proceed as usual:

 configure
 make
 su
 make install
 make distclean

!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

If you have problems to get started (does not compile or something else)
point your web browser to the subdirectory where the handbook resides:

  kvoctrain/docs/en/index.html
  
=========================================================================

Wenn Du schon Schwierigkeiten hast, überhaupt zu starten (z.B. kompiliert
nicht) lass Dir von deinem Webbrowser das Handbuch im folgenden
Unterverzeichnis anzeigen:

  kvoctrain/docs/de/index.html

!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

Happy learning,
